reviews.review_text: Pinnacle of '81 This is what the band sounds like when they are out to truly impress and then the stars align perfectly right.  This source from Steve Rolfe and Charlie Miller is WAY better than the MOTB version.  The highlights are just too many, but to get idea how screamin' this is from the start check out the instrumental section of Stranger.  It only gets better and better: the musical equivalent of pulling down the one-armed bandit and it comes up cherries and bars and gold coins are spilling all over the floor in heaps.  Best of 1981 and arguably the best MSG show they ever played.  This means fasten your seat belt Dorothy, 'cause Kansas is going bye-bye.
... This is, so, so, so, so, so, so, freaking awesome. My lord Jerry is just literally himself crackling with electricity, and sending it to everyone else though his tubez. WOW!
my first show!!!!!!! This was my first show n besides march 1981 at the hartford civic center i think this is one of the best the boys were just electrifying that night!!!!!!!!!
great show Bird Song and China/Rider are excellent! compare with 3/3/81

What a show! My fourth Dead show, and it was smokin' hot, just like the next night at MSG.  China -Rider is really really good, with a one-of-a-kind joyous meandering transition.  Rolls nicely into Samson.  UJB is always a sweet selection.  Cool space with a Terrapin tease, then Weir rocks Other One.  Nice Stella Blue, you can almost hear a pin drop in the audience.  If I could give it six stars, I would.  Get this one!
